Member of the House of Representatives, representing Ondo East and West Federal Constituency, Hon Abiola Makinde has appointed Mrs Adegboyega Ajanaku Ajibola as Special Assistant on Women affairs. This was made known to newsmen in a statement issued by his Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Prince Segun Adesemoye. Until her appointment, Mrs Ajibola was the Central senatorial Women leader of ADC in Ondo State. She was an active member of the Legislatorâ€™s campaign committee for the 2019 elections. Mrs Ajibola is to lead all women groups, coordinate their activities and be responsible for advancing their interest in Ondo East and West Federal Constituency The appointment is with immediate effect.